The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Nation | Nation Briefs
                                                                                                                                 2                                                                                        NATION BRIEFS
                                      
	 New Delhi, Dec 26 (PTI): A Delhi court has filed a complaint against four police personnel, including an inspector, and others for implicating four men in a false robbery case saying it involved serious constitutional and human rights violations.           
	Additional Sessions Judge Kamini Lau also issued notice to the Delhi government seeking its response as to why compensation should not be provided to the four men who were acquitted in the case.                   
	 New Delhi (PTI): A ship carrying over 25 Pakistani and Iraqis has been detained off Lakshadweep by security agencies after it illegally entered Indian waters. Sources suspect it was moving towards the Maldives. A team from Delhi has been rushed to the island to quiz the crew.                  
	 New Delhi (PTI): Delhi Metro will introduce a round-the-clock helpline number from January that will allow commuters to register their complaints and suggestions about the services. The number 155363 will replace 128128. The number was changed after complaints that the helpline could not be contacted from cellphones.                   
	 Rameswaram (PTI): Sixteen people, mostly local fishermen, were drowned when their boat capsized near Vazhai Theevu island in the Gulf of Mannar off Tamil Nadu, police said. The boat was carrying more than 20 people.                  
	 New Delhi (PTI): A youth was arrested for allegedly killing his cousins wife after she scolded him for indulging in celebratory firing during a family event in Delhi, police said. Anil Dagar was arrested from Dhansa Stand in Najafgarh after a tip off, police said. Dagar had shot Amita on December 17 at a relatives house.                   
	 Kotdwara (PTI): A leopard died after being hit by a vehicle in the Lansdowne forest division in Uttarakhands Pauri Garhwal on Friday, forest officials said.                                                                                                                                              
